This paper proposes a method for learning robust options in uncertain environments, which involves dealing with Markov decision processes and policy gradient methods. These topics are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
